29/06/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- President Branko Crvenkovski met with Serbian counterpart Boris Tadic on Wednesday (28 June), as part of Tadic's ongoing tour of the region. They agreed that Macedonia and Serbia must enhance collaboration and back each other on the road to EU integration. According to Crvenkovski, Macedonia supports the UN-mediated negotiations between Belgrade and Pristina aimed at settling the Kosovo status issue and would accept any solution that does not jeopardise Macedonia's sovereignty and territorial integrity. (RTS, Macedonian Radio, A1 TV, Telma TV - 28/06/06)
